race.comment: SALUTED (9) is a lightly raced filly who looked good winning her first two starts, including her second outing at this track over 1000m. She's come back to earth a bit since then and was poor last time at Sandown Hillside as a $3.20 chance but she's open to further improvement and can bounce back quickly. ONE HARD LADY (8) resumes with a nice profile. She won her first three in country NSW, measuring up quite well in Melbourne in two subsequent runs. She can kick up from the inside gate and if she holds the lead she'll go close. TARPAULIN (5) has been disappointing of late but his best would just about win this, watch the betting. CALL TO GLORY (1) is a speedy type who lands in a good spot here and will take catching.
